"6:6:8" : {s: 6, a: 6, w: 8, r: "قرن", t: "قَرْنٍۢ", l: "قَرْن", lc: 23, tl: "qarnin", lb: "যুগ",e: "generations", b: "কত জাতিকে", i: "kurun", f: 5, rm: "to join one thing with another, couple. qarnin/qarnan - generation, century. qarn (dual qarnani, oblique qaraini, plu. qurun) - horn, trumpet. Often used to symbolise strength/power/glory. qarunun (pl. qurana) - mate, comrade, intimate companion. muqarranin - bound together. muqrinina - capable of subduing. muqtarinin - those formed in serried ranks, accompanying ones.", ag: "أسم نكرة", eg: "Noun Indefinite state", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "INDEF", qual: "GEN", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: "قَرِينٌۭ"},
